1
00:00:04,504 --> 00:00:08,307
<i>In 2026, I, Kosei Neo,</i>

2
00:00:08,308 --> 00:00:09,609
<i>president of NEOXIS,</i>

3
00:00:10,176 --> 00:00:13,946
<i>should have died when someone pushed me…</i>

4
00:00:13,947 --> 00:00:17,282
<i>I ended up in the body of Eito Nomoto,
who looked just like me</i>

5
00:00:17,283 --> 00:00:18,951
<i>and was supposed to have died</i>

6
00:00:18,952 --> 00:00:20,652
<i>in an accident in 2012.</i>

7
00:00:20,653 --> 00:00:24,357
<i>He was the son of Eiji Nomoto,
the man caught in my fall.</i>

8
00:00:24,924 --> 00:00:28,160
<i>By living as Eito Nomoto,</i>

9
00:00:28,161 --> 00:00:31,498
<i>I begin to change the fate
of those around me.</i>

10
00:00:32,465 --> 00:00:35,635
<i>I couldn't take my eyes off her.</i>

11
00:00:37,170 --> 00:00:39,905
<i>Could it be… love?</i>

12
00:00:39,906 --> 00:00:40,807
<i>Also,</i>

13
00:00:42,075 --> 00:00:45,078
<i>who is the person who tried to kill me?</i>

14
00:00:47,414 --> 00:00:48,313
AKARI SHOPPING STREET

15
00:00:48,314 --> 00:00:49,715
SPRING OF 2017

16
00:00:49,716 --> 00:00:52,017
<i>That day, the shopping street was holding</i>

17
00:00:52,018 --> 00:00:54,987
<i>a meeting about the spring festival.</i>

18
00:00:54,988 --> 00:00:56,221
The Red Shadow appeared!

19
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:57,656
Hey!

20
00:00:57,657 --> 00:01:00,526
- Hey, Tara!
- Wait!

21
00:01:00,527 --> 00:01:02,796
- Hey!
- Hey!

22
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:09,269
So…

23
00:01:10,603 --> 00:01:15,040
we'd now like to choose the honored chair
of the Spring Festival Committee.

24
00:01:15,041 --> 00:01:18,710
- We've been waiting!
- Yes!

25
00:01:18,711 --> 00:01:19,611
The festival chair

26
00:01:19,612 --> 00:01:22,281
is the great hero of the shopping street.

27
00:01:22,282 --> 00:01:25,751
- Who will it be this year?
- Who?

28
00:01:25,752 --> 00:01:28,587
So, for this year,

29
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,189
it should be the one

30
00:01:30,190 --> 00:01:32,024
who revitalized Akari Shopping Street--

31
00:01:32,025 --> 00:01:34,693
- This year, it's gotta be Eito!
- Yeah!

32
00:01:34,694 --> 00:01:35,894
No!

33
00:01:35,895 --> 00:01:38,697
- I worked hard as president--
- Eito loves festivals

34
00:01:38,698 --> 00:01:41,266
more than anything else!

35
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:42,668
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

36
00:01:42,669 --> 00:01:45,738
So it's settled. Eito it is!

37
00:01:48,074 --> 00:01:49,942
Here, this has everyone's input.

38
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,144
- So, we're counting on you!
- Counting on you!

39
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:53,512
- Counting on you!
- Okay!

40
00:01:53,513 --> 00:01:56,415
Come on, everyone! Here's inari sushi!

41
00:01:56,416 --> 00:01:58,016
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

42
00:01:58,017 --> 00:01:59,785
Eat up, everyone!

43
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:02,054
- Here you go.
- Here.

44
00:02:02,055 --> 00:02:03,689
- Thank you, Sarasa!
- Okay.

45
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:05,023
- Thank you, Sarasa!
- Yes.

46
00:02:05,024 --> 00:02:07,526
- Thank you, Sarasa!
- Thank you, Sarasa!

47
00:02:07,527 --> 00:02:10,028
- Thank you, Sarasa!
- Thank you!

48
00:02:10,029 --> 00:02:11,964
- Okay.
- Thank you, Sarasa!

49
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:14,300
Have you fallen for someone else?

50
00:02:18,004 --> 00:02:20,306
<i>Has she been hung up
on that this whole time?</i>

51
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,942
"I want karaage."

52
00:02:23,943 --> 00:02:26,111
"A few kinds, like salted and sauced."

53
00:02:26,112 --> 00:02:27,913
"Figure out the right ratio

54
00:02:27,914 --> 00:02:31,550
of cabbage to bean sprouts
in the yakisoba."

55
00:02:31,551 --> 00:02:33,585
"Should the finale of the Yagura dance be

56
00:02:33,586 --> 00:02:36,555
<i>Tokyo Ondo</i> or <i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i>?"

57
00:02:36,556 --> 00:02:38,624
I don't care.

58
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:40,560
Honestly, I couldn't care less.

59
00:02:53,339 --> 00:02:56,142
Get out of my world this instant.

60
00:02:57,377 --> 00:03:00,146
<i>Under normal circumstances, I…</i>

61
00:03:00,847 --> 00:03:01,915
<i>ECONOMY COMPASS</i>
NEOXIS PRESIDENT KOSEI NEO

62
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:08,120
I'm sorry.
President Neo's schedule is very tight.

63
00:03:08,121 --> 00:03:10,656
I apologize. Please let me reschedule.

64
00:03:10,657 --> 00:03:11,858
Goodbye.

65
00:03:13,493 --> 00:03:15,060
Sounds tough.

66
00:03:15,061 --> 00:03:18,731
Since we entered the semiconductor
business, I've been flooded with requests.

67
00:03:19,999 --> 00:03:23,202
By the way, about that building site
the president had his eye on…

68
00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:24,836
With Togo's support,

69
00:03:24,837 --> 00:03:26,806
we've secured
the first right to negotiate.

70
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:30,109
Really? President Neo will be thrilled!

71
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:34,513
Togo should be reaching out soon.
Could you handle that as well?

72
00:03:34,514 --> 00:03:35,515
Yes.

73
00:03:44,991 --> 00:03:46,759
Good morning, President Nagamine.

74
00:03:48,161 --> 00:03:50,296
A semiconductor conference
in Silicon Valley?

75
00:03:51,130 --> 00:03:53,466
Starting next week,
for two nights, three days.

76
00:03:56,836 --> 00:04:00,406
I have to reschedule everything!

77
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:10,516
I somehow managed to see Mr. Neo off.

78
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:14,988
Okay.

79
00:04:18,625 --> 00:04:20,993
Hello, Tomono? Did something happen?

80
00:04:20,994 --> 00:04:22,929
<i>I'm trying to contact Mr. Neo.</i>

81
00:04:23,529 --> 00:04:26,765
I wanted to discuss the venue
for the day-after-tomorrow's

82
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:27,800
building site negotiation.

83
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:33,205
Neo's in Silicon Valley?

84
00:04:33,206 --> 00:04:35,140
I'm terribly sorry. This was our mistake.

85
00:04:35,141 --> 00:04:37,210
- It was my fault!
- Just be quiet for a moment!

86
00:04:39,312 --> 00:04:40,413
This is a problem.

87
00:04:42,248 --> 00:04:44,651
I worked so hard
to arrange this negotiation.

88
00:04:46,719 --> 00:04:50,656
Is there any way to reschedule it
for after he returns?

89
00:04:50,657 --> 00:04:53,959
No. If we miss that date, the right

90
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:57,297
to negotiate passes
to another top candidate.

91
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:00,466
So…

92
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,169
we won't be able to get the property?

93
00:05:03,736 --> 00:05:06,072
Opportunity doesn't wait!

94
00:05:07,607 --> 00:05:08,441
Oh!

95
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:11,177
My brother is available!

96
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:13,679
How about using my brother

97
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:16,416
who looks like President Neo
to handle the negotiation?

98
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:20,852
Nomoto, what are you saying?
Please, just be quiet.

99
00:05:20,853 --> 00:05:21,887
But…

100
00:05:21,888 --> 00:05:24,324
Actually… that might work.

101
00:05:25,658 --> 00:05:26,758
What?

102
00:05:26,759 --> 00:05:27,960
Eito might just be able

103
00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:30,662
to pull it off.

104
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:31,863
Wait a moment.

105
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:34,667
If he's exposed as a fake,
it could leave a bad impression.

106
00:05:35,601 --> 00:05:38,270
But if we cancel the negotiation,

107
00:05:38,271 --> 00:05:40,340
we won't get the building site anyway.

108
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:44,843
But if the decoy becomes public knowledge,
President Neo will take the heat.

109
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:46,546
That's why you're here!

110
00:05:47,647 --> 00:05:51,117
It'll be worth watching
how Eito handles himself.

111
00:05:52,218 --> 00:05:54,286
But what will President Neo say?

112
00:05:54,287 --> 00:05:57,790
Neo will do whatever it takes
to get that land at any cost!

113
00:06:01,928 --> 00:06:05,831
Turtles have always been
a symbol of good fortune!

114
00:06:05,832 --> 00:06:09,368
Turtle scooping is the obvious choice!
Right, Kamaitachi? I mean, guys?

115
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:11,203
What are you talking about?

116
00:06:11,204 --> 00:06:14,206
Goldfish are the symbol of good fortune!

117
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:18,276
Everybody knows festivals
have always meant goldfish scooping!

118
00:06:18,277 --> 00:06:20,679
- Um… how about doing both?
- Yeah.

119
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,914
We only have one tank!

120
00:06:22,915 --> 00:06:24,583
- Oh, come on!
- Calm down!

121
00:06:24,584 --> 00:06:27,487
- Jeez…
- Don't get mad!

122
00:06:29,055 --> 00:06:31,790
You know, I keep thinking…

123
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,558
For the Yagura dance finale,

124
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,926
it's gotta be <i>Tokyo Ondo</i>.

125
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:38,430
What are you saying?
It should be <i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i>!

126
00:06:38,431 --> 00:06:40,566
- What?
- Um… how about both songs?

127
00:06:41,134 --> 00:06:43,268
The finale should be one song!

128
00:06:43,269 --> 00:06:45,203
- Jeez…
- Now, now…

129
00:06:45,204 --> 00:06:47,839
How about Eito makes
the final call as chairperson?

130
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,474
We're leaving it to you.

131
00:06:49,475 --> 00:06:51,143
<i>Even if you leave it to me,</i>

132
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:52,911
<i>it's so trivial, I honestly can't decide.</i>

133
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,212
Does everyone have enough to drink?

134
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:55,380
- Me too.
- Yes.

135
00:06:55,381 --> 00:06:56,648
- I'll get it.
- Yes.

136
00:06:56,649 --> 00:07:00,019
Thank you, Sarasa!

137
00:07:01,821 --> 00:07:03,088
<i>Is this really okay?</i>

138
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,289
Thank you, Sarasa!

139
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:07,326
<i>- If this is a forbidden love…</i>
- Drink up!

140
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:10,496
<i>…I could just let it end right here.</i>

141
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,834
<i>And yet,</i>

142
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:18,871
<i>the colder she is to me,
the more I can't stop thinking about her.</i>

143
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:22,007
Welcome home.

144
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:23,676
- Welcome home.
- Welcome home.

145
00:07:26,679 --> 00:07:29,448
Brother, we need to talk.

146
00:07:29,449 --> 00:07:31,716
- What's up?
- I'd also like to ask you something.

147
00:07:31,717 --> 00:07:33,085
- Huh?
- All right.

148
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,554
- What?
- Sorry.

149
00:07:35,555 --> 00:07:36,923
- Yeah.
- Okay.

150
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,990
A decoy?

151
00:07:38,991 --> 00:07:42,161
We'd like you to play
the role of President Neo.

152
00:07:42,895 --> 00:07:45,297
Me as President Neo?

153
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,332
I'm sorry for the weird request.

154
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,868
I know you hate lying,

155
00:07:49,869 --> 00:07:51,204
but I'm in a real bind here.

156
00:07:52,438 --> 00:07:55,741
<i>I mean, I am Kosei Neo,
so it's not really a lie.</i>

157
00:07:56,542 --> 00:07:59,178
The fate of our office building
is riding on this.

158
00:08:00,079 --> 00:08:01,747
<i>And our own office building…</i>

159
00:08:02,548 --> 00:08:06,385
<i>It was Kosei Neo's long-cherished wish,
ever since President Ichimanda</i>

160
00:08:06,953 --> 00:08:08,754
<i>took his dad's building.</i>

161
00:08:09,355 --> 00:08:10,856
<i>And if this opportunity also helps</i>

162
00:08:10,857 --> 00:08:14,426
<i>Eri and Tomono's romance along…</i>

163
00:08:14,427 --> 00:08:17,096
Good morning, sir.

164
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:21,868
<i>…then the forbidden night scandal
can be avoided too.</i>

165
00:08:24,437 --> 00:08:28,007
<i>If this lets me skip the festival,
it's a blessing in disguise.</i>

166
00:08:31,711 --> 00:08:32,978
Dad.

167
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,947
Dad, I have a favor to ask.

168
00:08:35,948 --> 00:08:39,485
I want to hand the festival
committee chairmanship over to you.

169
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:42,054
Oh? Is that okay?

170
00:08:42,755 --> 00:08:45,724
When I think about it, the chairperson

171
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:48,361
should really be you,
the president of Akari Shopping Street.

172
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:53,165
I guess. Well, if you insist, Eito,

173
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:55,001
I suppose I have no choice.

174
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:58,503
Well, if Eito says so…

175
00:08:58,504 --> 00:09:00,138
We can't oppose it.

176
00:09:00,139 --> 00:09:01,940
So you will…

177
00:09:01,941 --> 00:09:03,476
Agree to do it?

178
00:09:04,076 --> 00:09:06,845
If it's for my little sister

179
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:07,713
and Tomono, then sure.

180
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,231
Hey, you!

181
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:28,500
- Again?
- <i>Oh, no!</i>

182
00:09:28,501 --> 00:09:30,035
- To the police…
- No!

183
00:09:30,036 --> 00:09:30,970
Please come with us to security.

184
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:34,773
Sorry.

185
00:09:34,774 --> 00:09:37,142
This gentleman is a VIP of NEOXIS.

186
00:09:37,143 --> 00:09:38,644
What? A VIP?

187
00:09:39,679 --> 00:09:42,248
I sincerely apologize
for the inconvenience!

188
00:09:46,719 --> 00:09:48,854
Nice to meet you.

189
00:09:50,723 --> 00:09:52,959
This is the president's office.

190
00:10:12,979 --> 00:10:14,213
<i>So nostalgic…</i>

191
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:19,184
- Is it okay?
- Yeah.

192
00:10:19,185 --> 00:10:20,385
Okay.

193
00:10:20,386 --> 00:10:22,622
This decoy plan must be kept
completely secret.

194
00:10:23,189 --> 00:10:26,324
Only we know that President Neo is abroad.

195
00:10:26,325 --> 00:10:29,695
For the three days until the president
returns to Japan, you're Kosei Neo.

196
00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:32,865
<i>After all, I am Kosei Neo.</i>

197
00:10:33,432 --> 00:10:36,334
Change into his suit.

198
00:10:36,335 --> 00:10:37,536
Yeah.

199
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:39,472
<i>ECONOMY COMPASS</i>
NEOXIS PRESIDENT KOSEI NEO

200
00:10:42,875 --> 00:10:45,910
- I'll style your hair to match his.
- Okay.

201
00:10:45,911 --> 00:10:47,380
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

202
00:10:49,482 --> 00:10:50,716
Like this…

203
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:55,053
- Wasn't it like this?
- Um…

204
00:10:55,054 --> 00:10:57,490
- I'll do it.
- Okay.

205
00:10:59,258 --> 00:11:01,761
- Okay.
- And finally, the glasses.

206
00:11:03,195 --> 00:11:05,964
Wow, the resemblance is incredible!

207
00:11:05,965 --> 00:11:08,167
I didn't expect them
to look this much alike.

208
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:12,370
Unlike you, President Neo is composed.

209
00:11:12,371 --> 00:11:14,807
So you'll need to learn
his speech and mannerisms too.

210
00:11:15,741 --> 00:11:18,376
<i>It's simply natural
that e-commerce and subscriptions</i>

211
00:11:18,377 --> 00:11:21,046
<i>are killing off</i>

212
00:11:21,047 --> 00:11:22,581
<i>online and physical shops.</i>

213
00:11:23,249 --> 00:11:26,819
<i>Watching it again like this
is a bit embarrassing.</i>

214
00:11:27,953 --> 00:11:29,055
<i>"For the people."</i>

215
00:11:29,755 --> 00:11:32,291
<i>That's all that matters.</i>

216
00:11:34,894 --> 00:11:37,862
"For the people." That's all that matters.

217
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:39,130
- Okay, once more.
- Okay.

218
00:11:39,131 --> 00:11:41,966
<i>To give up or to achieve…</i>

219
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:45,271
<i>When you ask yourself which is more fun,
the answer is obvious.</i>

220
00:11:46,405 --> 00:11:48,306
To give up or to achieve…

221
00:11:48,307 --> 00:11:51,276
When you ask yourself which is more fun,
the answer is obvious.

222
00:11:51,277 --> 00:11:52,945
<i>It may sound extreme,
but if you truly want</i>

223
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:56,214
<i>to change yourself, I've heard you should</i>

224
00:11:56,215 --> 00:12:00,019
<i>replace all the people closest to you.</i>

225
00:12:01,253 --> 00:12:05,424
I've heard you should replace
all the people closest to you.

226
00:12:06,358 --> 00:12:08,994
The arrogance and selfishness
come through too.

227
00:12:10,129 --> 00:12:13,866
As does the sense that
he doesn't consider others' situations.

228
00:12:15,034 --> 00:12:15,868
I see.

229
00:12:16,435 --> 00:12:19,704
The mission is to, as President Neo,

230
00:12:19,705 --> 00:12:23,975
finalize the land purchase negotiation
with Shino Real Estate for our building.

231
00:12:23,976 --> 00:12:26,111
If we agree on the contract terms

232
00:12:26,112 --> 00:12:28,247
by tomorrow and sign it the next day,
it's a success.

233
00:12:28,881 --> 00:12:31,484
Here are the files
on the negotiating party.

234
00:12:32,685 --> 00:12:33,918
<i>Ai Shinomiya.</i>

235
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,819
SHINO REAL ESTATE
AI SHINOMIYA

236
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:38,991
<i>Of course.
I did that kind of deal with her…</i>

237
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:43,561
She's the Shino Real Estate
president's daughter and a director.

238
00:12:43,562 --> 00:12:46,030
She and President Neo are the same age.

239
00:12:46,031 --> 00:12:48,867
Shinomiya is also involved
in welfare work,

240
00:12:48,868 --> 00:12:50,702
and she and President Neo crossed paths

241
00:12:50,703 --> 00:12:52,370
during the Great East Japan Quake,

242
00:12:52,371 --> 00:12:54,907
so I've included details
about that connection as well.

243
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,276
<i>I see…</i>

244
00:12:58,244 --> 00:13:00,012
<i>Back then, she and I…</i>

245
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:03,414
- Yes?
- Huh?

246
00:13:03,415 --> 00:13:07,219
- Huh?
- What?

247
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:09,488
- Huh?
- What?

248
00:13:10,222 --> 00:13:11,289
- Excuse me.
- Sorry!

249
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:12,390
- We're tied up now.
- No!

250
00:13:12,391 --> 00:13:13,491
- This is urgent!
- Hey!

251
00:13:13,492 --> 00:13:15,561
- Please come later!
- We'll be quick!

252
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:18,630
Excuse me.

253
00:13:18,631 --> 00:13:21,833
These are alternative property options

254
00:13:21,834 --> 00:13:23,368
in case the negotiation falls through.

255
00:13:23,369 --> 00:13:25,804
Tsuchiya, do you expect me

256
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:28,139
to fail the negotiation?

257
00:13:28,140 --> 00:13:30,141
No! That's not what I meant…

258
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:32,545
Then we don't need this.

259
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:34,880
I sincerely apologize.

260
00:13:36,182 --> 00:13:38,917
Also, regarding
the office building construction…

261
00:13:38,918 --> 00:13:40,885
To realize your vision, we'd significantly

262
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:42,554
exceed the estimated budget.

263
00:13:42,555 --> 00:13:44,656
Isn't securing that money

264
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,391
your job?

265
00:13:46,392 --> 00:13:49,260
But we've sunk too much capital
into semiconductors…

266
00:13:49,261 --> 00:13:52,730
Build the office building of our dreams,

267
00:13:52,731 --> 00:13:55,768
or leave the company…
Choose whichever sounds more fun.

268
00:13:57,903 --> 00:14:01,606
- I'll go negotiate with the main bank.
- Please.

269
00:14:01,607 --> 00:14:02,775
Excuse me.

270
00:14:31,904 --> 00:14:36,007
<i>I remember now… That contract negotiation…</i>

271
00:14:36,008 --> 00:14:37,075
PREVIOUS LIFE IN 2017

272
00:14:37,076 --> 00:14:41,113
Regarding the purchase price,
would the amount in the proposal be fine?

273
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:46,619
You've got some nerve.

274
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:51,357
For a mere startup, no less.

275
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:55,060
Everyone's entitled to their own opinion.

276
00:14:55,628 --> 00:14:57,629
Talking to you somehow makes me

277
00:14:57,630 --> 00:14:59,865
angrier by the minute.

278
00:15:00,566 --> 00:15:03,202
I apologize for that.

279
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:05,838
But very well.

280
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,741
In light of your commitment to welfare,

281
00:15:09,441 --> 00:15:11,777
and the "For the People" spirit…

282
00:15:12,978 --> 00:15:16,682
I don't like the price,
but I'll sell it to you.

283
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:19,752
<i>Despite her complaints, she sold</i>

284
00:15:20,286 --> 00:15:22,354
- <i>to us at a bargain price.</i>
- Thank you.

285
00:15:24,023 --> 00:15:25,357
Still…

286
00:15:48,647 --> 00:15:51,483
I'm Tomono from NEOXIS.
I've brought President Neo.

287
00:15:52,051 --> 00:15:55,654
- We've been expecting you. Right this way.
- Excuse us.

288
00:15:56,588 --> 00:15:58,223
Excuse us.

289
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:06,498
<i>This room, her outfit…
It's all the same, like a déjà vu.</i>

290
00:16:09,034 --> 00:16:12,905
Regarding the purchase price,
would the amount in the proposal be fine?

291
00:16:16,508 --> 00:16:19,578
You've got some nerve.

292
00:16:20,579 --> 00:16:22,481
For a mere startup, no less.

293
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:26,985
Everyone's entitled to their own opinion.

294
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,287
Talking to you somehow makes me

295
00:16:29,288 --> 00:16:31,657
angrier by the minute.

296
00:16:32,224 --> 00:16:35,227
I apologize for that.

297
00:16:36,795 --> 00:16:38,697
<i>The same price as last time.</i>

298
00:16:39,798 --> 00:16:42,735
<i>By negotiating, I managed to get it
at an even bigger discount.</i>

299
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:45,704
I'm sorry.

300
00:16:47,406 --> 00:16:49,742
I'll need you to pay double.

301
00:16:51,043 --> 00:16:51,877
What?

302
00:16:53,412 --> 00:16:54,880
<i>What is this?</i>

303
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,583
<i>This didn't happen
in the previous negotiation.</i>

304
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:02,453
But the preliminary talks
established this price…

305
00:17:02,454 --> 00:17:03,956
Things have changed.

306
00:17:04,923 --> 00:17:08,259
A company willing to pay double
has come forward.

307
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:09,728
And which company is that?

308
00:17:11,296 --> 00:17:13,664
If I say it's the top company

309
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:15,501
in your industry,

310
00:17:16,135 --> 00:17:18,103
would you understand?

311
00:17:20,172 --> 00:17:22,941
Is that President Ichimanda's company,
Soman?

312
00:17:29,048 --> 00:17:30,182
<i>Good grief.</i>

313
00:17:31,183 --> 00:17:33,852
<i>Because NEOXIS
and Soman's history changed…</i>

314
00:17:34,686 --> 00:17:36,721
But…

315
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:39,558
at double the price,
it would be quite difficult…

316
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:45,163
- Let me call the president.
- What do you mean?

317
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:47,466
He's right here, isn't he?

318
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:51,670
Oh…

319
00:17:53,338 --> 00:17:54,272
No…

320
00:17:54,273 --> 00:17:56,442
She meant the president
of the lending company.

321
00:18:02,181 --> 00:18:03,415
Go right ahead.

322
00:18:04,283 --> 00:18:05,984
Could we have a few moments, then?

323
00:18:20,732 --> 00:18:22,634
Now it's just the two of us.

324
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:25,971
Yeah.

325
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:28,707
Let's wait for the lender's response.

326
00:18:31,743 --> 00:18:33,078
It brings back memories.

327
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,682
You know, five years ago…

328
00:18:37,316 --> 00:18:39,150
<i>During the disaster relief work…</i>

329
00:18:39,151 --> 00:18:40,051
DISASTER VICTIMS NETWORK
FOR THE PEOPLE

330
00:18:40,052 --> 00:18:43,421
<i>After the soup kitchen, we talked</i>

331
00:18:43,422 --> 00:18:45,724
<i>about the future of the disaster area.</i>

332
00:18:46,758 --> 00:18:48,626
<i>And then,</i>

333
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,762
<i>we had dinner together.</i>

334
00:18:52,498 --> 00:18:54,867
Did we?

335
00:18:57,336 --> 00:18:58,504
Do you remember that time?

336
00:18:59,771 --> 00:19:02,241
Of course I do.

337
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:06,345
It was good, wasn't it?

338
00:19:07,846 --> 00:19:11,116
<i>Delicious? What did we eat?</i>

339
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:16,088
Do you remember what we ate?

340
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:26,365
Don't tell me…

341
00:19:27,466 --> 00:19:30,169
you forgot?

342
00:19:32,738 --> 00:19:33,672
No.

343
00:19:34,406 --> 00:19:36,642
<i>I've completely ruined the impression.</i>

344
00:19:37,309 --> 00:19:38,710
<i>This is a seriously bad development.</i>

345
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:42,915
Excuse me.

346
00:19:44,082 --> 00:19:45,617
Sir, may I have a moment?

347
00:19:46,552 --> 00:19:48,687
Excuse me. I'll be back.

348
00:19:51,223 --> 00:19:54,058
What should we do? I can't reach him.

349
00:19:54,059 --> 00:19:56,060
<i>The real problem right now</i>

350
00:19:56,061 --> 00:19:58,063
<i>is what we ate that day.</i>

351
00:19:58,664 --> 00:20:00,465
<i>Remember!</i>

352
00:20:01,266 --> 00:20:02,166
Oh!

353
00:20:02,167 --> 00:20:03,501
<i>It's like…</i>

354
00:20:03,502 --> 00:20:05,204
<i>The more I try to remember, my head…</i>

355
00:20:06,171 --> 00:20:08,139
<i>What is this headache?</i>

356
00:20:08,140 --> 00:20:10,374
Yeah!

357
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:11,376
Ah!

358
00:20:12,644 --> 00:20:14,078
Nice catch!

359
00:20:14,079 --> 00:20:17,683
HAMBURGER

360
00:20:26,592 --> 00:20:27,693
Excuse us.

361
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:36,367
Shall we continue the discussion
about the purchase price?

362
00:20:36,368 --> 00:20:40,606
Before that, I'd like to finish
my conversation with Neo.

363
00:20:43,108 --> 00:20:43,942
Sorry.

364
00:20:45,143 --> 00:20:46,612
I wasn't forgetting…

365
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:50,215
back there.

366
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:54,953
I was remembering what happened that day.

367
00:20:59,024 --> 00:21:00,425
You saw me

368
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:04,763
<i>cutting my burger with a knife and fork</i>

369
00:21:05,864 --> 00:21:06,999
<i>and found it amusing.</i>

370
00:21:09,534 --> 00:21:11,669
Eating it that way makes it feel

371
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:13,605
like a fancy meal.

372
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:17,709
This is fancy enough.

373
00:21:24,716 --> 00:21:27,586
- Can I try it too?
- Yeah.

374
00:21:44,269 --> 00:21:45,637
Nice.

375
00:21:47,906 --> 00:21:50,275
It would be great
if we had a glass of red wine.

376
00:21:51,943 --> 00:21:53,111
I have some.

377
00:22:01,286 --> 00:22:02,354
What?

378
00:22:03,722 --> 00:22:06,524
I still sometimes eat that way

379
00:22:06,525 --> 00:22:08,360
to this day.

380
00:22:09,961 --> 00:22:12,864
I've been hooked on that wine ever since.

381
00:22:13,465 --> 00:22:14,666
Is that so?

382
00:22:16,201 --> 00:22:18,036
I remember your words too.

383
00:22:18,704 --> 00:22:19,671
Huh?

384
00:22:20,539 --> 00:22:24,409
Working in welfare
has taught me something.

385
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:30,247
To help those in need,

386
00:22:30,248 --> 00:22:33,185
you have to have the strength
to help them.

387
00:22:34,853 --> 00:22:36,855
So I have to work hard.

388
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:44,563
Well, I'll do my best too.

389
00:22:46,732 --> 00:22:49,601
To help those in need,

390
00:22:50,335 --> 00:22:52,938
you need the strength to do so.

391
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,608
But I worried that

392
00:22:57,976 --> 00:23:01,546
the people I helped
wouldn't always be grateful.

393
00:23:03,782 --> 00:23:05,851
Some might not even realize
they'd been helped…

394
00:23:09,354 --> 00:23:11,456
and might even resent you for it.

395
00:23:13,325 --> 00:23:14,426
In moments like that,

396
00:23:17,129 --> 00:23:19,831
I wanted the kind of strength

397
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,268
to still stand firm.

398
00:23:24,903 --> 00:23:25,837
But back then,

399
00:23:26,872 --> 00:23:28,373
your pure passion

400
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,909
made me feel

401
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:34,813
ashamed of my own thinking.

402
00:23:36,948 --> 00:23:40,852
So I said, "Well, I'll do my best too."

403
00:23:42,721 --> 00:23:44,356
You didn't just do your best…

404
00:23:46,892 --> 00:23:50,061
I think you went on
to do far more than just your best.

405
00:23:52,798 --> 00:23:54,266
<i>What is this feeling?</i>

406
00:23:55,901 --> 00:23:58,537
<i>The way she's looking at me
is different from before.</i>

407
00:24:01,306 --> 00:24:02,774
Now you're the rising star

408
00:24:03,542 --> 00:24:07,379
of the startup world,
even venturing into semiconductors.

409
00:24:10,682 --> 00:24:13,852
I have great admiration for you.

410
00:24:19,658 --> 00:24:22,726
Now, about the purchase price…

411
00:24:22,727 --> 00:24:24,062
I'll leave

412
00:24:25,063 --> 00:24:26,832
the rest to Shinomiya.

413
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:29,067
- Huh?
- Huh?

414
00:24:29,901 --> 00:24:33,437
I'm looking forward

415
00:24:33,438 --> 00:24:35,240
to the final negotiation tomorrow.

416
00:24:37,142 --> 00:24:38,276
Likewise.

417
00:24:40,412 --> 00:24:41,846
Well…

418
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:44,548
I think we managed to pull through.

419
00:24:44,549 --> 00:24:47,651
What do you think you're doing?
Do you know what you just agreed to?

420
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:51,522
Accepting double the budget
is not feasible.

421
00:24:51,523 --> 00:24:54,392
That's not what we agreed to.

422
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:56,093
Huh?

423
00:24:56,094 --> 00:24:59,764
For these three days, I am President Neo.

424
00:25:02,133 --> 00:25:04,235
And if I were President Neo,

425
00:25:04,236 --> 00:25:06,705
I wouldn't flinch at a price like that.

426
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:14,379
- A reply from President Neo.
- What does it say?

427
00:25:15,714 --> 00:25:17,414
"Spend whatever it takes."

428
00:25:17,415 --> 00:25:19,251
"Just make sure we get it."

429
00:25:20,285 --> 00:25:21,286
I was right.

430
00:25:22,521 --> 00:25:24,222
Just like my brother said.

431
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:26,791
Eito…

432
00:25:28,460 --> 00:25:30,495
There's something I've been wondering…

433
00:25:31,429 --> 00:25:33,497
The story about the two of you

434
00:25:33,498 --> 00:25:35,734
having dinner, which wasn't in our files…

435
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:39,304
why were you able
to talk about it so naturally?

436
00:25:42,340 --> 00:25:43,808
A hunch, I guess.

437
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:50,147
Tomorrow, we'll meet at 10:00 a.m.

438
00:25:50,148 --> 00:25:51,782
We'll leave from the office,

439
00:25:51,783 --> 00:25:53,384
so don't be late.

440
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:54,352
Yes.

441
00:25:55,153 --> 00:25:58,356
AKARI SHOPPING STREET

442
00:26:01,092 --> 00:26:01,927
Hey!

443
00:26:02,627 --> 00:26:05,062
What are we doing, Mr. Committee Chair?

444
00:26:05,063 --> 00:26:08,499
The festival's coming up,
and nothing has been decided yet!

445
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:11,101
That's why I'm planning

446
00:26:11,102 --> 00:26:13,971
a headline event to further promote

447
00:26:13,972 --> 00:26:16,106
Akari Shopping Street,
now a popular destination!

448
00:26:16,107 --> 00:26:19,476
Paying big money to bring in
a celebrity is ridiculous!

449
00:26:19,477 --> 00:26:22,012
It would've been better
if Eito was chairperson.

450
00:26:22,013 --> 00:26:24,615
- Yeah!
- I guess

451
00:26:24,616 --> 00:26:26,917
running a festival is just beyond you.

452
00:26:26,918 --> 00:26:28,953
- Right?
- Yeah.

453
00:26:28,954 --> 00:26:30,487
Then, you deal with it!

454
00:26:30,488 --> 00:26:33,090
"Then, you deal with it!"

455
00:26:33,091 --> 00:26:34,425
- Hey!
- Eiji!

456
00:26:34,426 --> 00:26:35,559
- It's okay!
- Huh?

457
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:36,894
- Huh?
- He went out front.

458
00:26:36,895 --> 00:26:37,795
He got angry.

459
00:26:37,796 --> 00:26:39,330
He's so childish!

460
00:26:39,331 --> 00:26:40,698
- You said too much!
- But…

461
00:26:40,699 --> 00:26:41,732
Why is

462
00:26:41,733 --> 00:26:43,267
the festival-loving Eito not here?

463
00:26:43,268 --> 00:26:44,768
Eri said he had something

464
00:26:44,769 --> 00:26:47,071
more important than the festival.

465
00:26:47,072 --> 00:26:48,539
- Huh?
- Could it be…

466
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:50,874
a forbidden love,
like the flower-petal fortune?

467
00:26:50,875 --> 00:26:51,842
Huh?

468
00:26:51,843 --> 00:26:53,444
Wait!

469
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:54,511
- Another woman?
- No!

470
00:26:54,512 --> 00:26:56,481
- No!
- Oh, I love that kind of story!

471
00:26:58,316 --> 00:26:59,417
Ow!

472
00:27:02,087 --> 00:27:02,987
Sorry.

473
00:27:02,988 --> 00:27:03,888
She's scary…

474
00:27:08,593 --> 00:27:10,761
Okay. I'm heading out.

475
00:27:10,762 --> 00:27:12,329
‎NOMOTO DRY CLEANERS

476
00:27:12,330 --> 00:27:13,398
Keep it between us.

477
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:18,369
- I'm telling you it's good…
- Oh!

478
00:27:18,370 --> 00:27:21,572
Eito, look at you all dressed up!

479
00:27:21,573 --> 00:27:23,540
Don't tell me it's a date!

480
00:27:23,541 --> 00:27:25,977
Someone’s "lively," huh?

481
00:27:27,145 --> 00:27:28,246
Oh…

482
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:29,913
Yeah… Um…

483
00:27:29,914 --> 00:27:32,783
Yeah… "Lively"…

484
00:27:32,784 --> 00:27:34,786
Don't worry about it!

485
00:27:50,235 --> 00:27:51,536
- Morning.
- Morning.

486
00:27:53,405 --> 00:27:56,307
Have a minute? I'd like to talk with you
before the negotiation.

487
00:28:14,159 --> 00:28:17,494
First, I owe you an apology.

488
00:28:17,495 --> 00:28:18,730
An apology?

489
00:28:20,498 --> 00:28:24,803
I said something awful to you
in the disaster zone. Do you remember?

490
00:28:26,137 --> 00:28:27,906
You're cold.

491
00:28:28,673 --> 00:28:30,775
You don't even try to understand people.

492
00:28:33,645 --> 00:28:35,212
<i>Back then,</i>

493
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,415
you kept provoking me,

494
00:28:38,683 --> 00:28:40,518
so I thought you had a grudge against me.

495
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:42,454
I'm sorry.

496
00:28:43,788 --> 00:28:47,258
Meeting you this time,
I realized I was wrong.

497
00:28:49,494 --> 00:28:53,130
From you, I feel a warm aura,

498
00:28:53,131 --> 00:28:55,100
one that truly cares for others.

499
00:28:57,235 --> 00:29:00,438
I'm… warm?

500
00:29:01,239 --> 00:29:03,540
<i>Is that because of how I've been engaging</i>

501
00:29:03,541 --> 00:29:05,410
<i>with the shopping street as Eito?</i>

502
00:29:06,544 --> 00:29:10,682
<i>Am I becoming less and less
like Kosei Neo?</i>

503
00:29:17,622 --> 00:29:18,723
That day…

504
00:29:20,792 --> 00:29:23,628
Do you know what I was feeling…

505
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:27,198
toward you?

506
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:29,701
<i>Looking into those eyes,</i>

507
00:29:30,468 --> 00:29:32,904
<i>a rush of memories from that day
came flooding back.</i>

508
00:29:35,907 --> 00:29:38,610
I think you're cold,

509
00:29:40,211 --> 00:29:42,514
but for some reason,
I can't take my eyes off you.

510
00:29:49,921 --> 00:29:53,390
This feeling I've never felt before…

511
00:29:53,391 --> 00:29:55,326
What is it?

512
00:29:59,731 --> 00:30:00,698
<i>No way…</i>

513
00:30:02,066 --> 00:30:04,002
<i>I couldn't see it then,</i>

514
00:30:04,869 --> 00:30:06,004
<i>but I can now.</i>

515
00:30:11,409 --> 00:30:12,243
Hey.

516
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,448
How do I look to you…

517
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:22,520
right now?

518
00:30:26,157 --> 00:30:27,425
Together,

519
00:30:27,959 --> 00:30:30,595
I think we could do
something wonderful for society.

520
00:30:35,233 --> 00:30:36,201
I'd…

521
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:39,070
like to go out with you.

522
00:30:41,005 --> 00:30:42,806
<i>For the sake of the office building,</i>

523
00:30:42,807 --> 00:30:45,643
<i>I suppose I have no choice
but to give a favorable answer for now.</i>

524
00:30:53,318 --> 00:30:57,655
Does that silence mean you're interested?

525
00:31:01,392 --> 00:31:02,560
I think…

526
00:31:04,562 --> 00:31:06,297
you're a wonderful person.

527
00:31:14,739 --> 00:31:16,040
But I'm sorry.

528
00:31:18,610 --> 00:31:19,510
There's someone…

529
00:31:22,747 --> 00:31:24,649
I have feelings for.

530
00:31:32,323 --> 00:31:34,458
So I can't--

531
00:31:34,459 --> 00:31:35,526
What kind of person?

532
00:31:40,665 --> 00:31:42,734
Someone who loves to paint…

533
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:44,636
and who cherishes…

534
00:31:46,604 --> 00:31:50,074
their hometown.

535
00:32:13,464 --> 00:32:14,866
Is that so?

536
00:32:19,037 --> 00:32:20,071
What a shame.

537
00:32:27,345 --> 00:32:29,147
<i>What am I doing?</i>

538
00:32:31,749 --> 00:32:35,453
<i>I could have just kept
her hopes up. Why did I…</i>

539
00:32:40,758 --> 00:32:43,827
Shinomiya, regarding the purchase price…

540
00:32:43,828 --> 00:32:45,430
Last night, I received a new offer

541
00:32:46,464 --> 00:32:48,865
from Soman

542
00:32:48,866 --> 00:32:52,403
at triple the price.

543
00:32:53,438 --> 00:32:54,605
<i>Triple?</i>

544
00:32:55,173 --> 00:32:59,277
Why does Soman want that land so badly?

545
00:32:59,944 --> 00:33:02,080
Because they don't like Kosei Neo

546
00:33:02,847 --> 00:33:04,382
and want to get in the way.

547
00:33:07,151 --> 00:33:10,121
I don't particularly like you either,
for that matter.

548
00:33:11,322 --> 00:33:12,623
<i>It's over.</i>

549
00:33:19,864 --> 00:33:21,833
<i>Because of me, the office building…</i>

550
00:33:25,036 --> 00:33:26,738
But I'll sell you that land.

551
00:33:52,630 --> 00:33:55,499
This is far below Soman's asking price.

552
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:57,101
It's the original asking price.

553
00:33:57,702 --> 00:33:58,703
Why?

554
00:34:00,905 --> 00:34:03,373
The people who come to me

555
00:34:03,374 --> 00:34:04,842
only ever say pretty things…

556
00:34:06,544 --> 00:34:10,348
only hollow flattery and compliments.

557
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:14,652
But you were different.

558
00:34:17,655 --> 00:34:19,257
You're an honest person,

559
00:34:20,691 --> 00:34:23,194
so I can trust you as a business partner.

560
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,369
Let's keep working together…

561
00:34:33,704 --> 00:34:35,506
for all kinds of people.

562
00:34:39,477 --> 00:34:42,213
- Thanks.
- Well done.

563
00:34:46,017 --> 00:34:49,020
Was what happened earlier
meant to test me?

564
00:34:50,688 --> 00:34:52,757
Let's just say…

565
00:34:53,891 --> 00:34:55,359
it was.

566
00:34:57,995 --> 00:34:59,564
- Ow.
- Oh.

567
00:35:01,199 --> 00:35:02,233
Okay!

568
00:35:06,304 --> 00:35:08,673
We did it! Mission accomplished!

569
00:35:10,575 --> 00:35:11,576
Ichimanda…

570
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:16,414
I received a message
from Ai Shinomiya. Congratulations.

571
00:35:17,615 --> 00:35:21,419
I'd appreciate it
if you would stop interfering from now on.

572
00:35:22,019 --> 00:35:24,355
Wasn't it you who interfered first?

573
00:35:25,089 --> 00:35:28,893
You’re a lowly thief
who stole my semiconductor business.

574
00:35:31,162 --> 00:35:34,565
Before that, you stole
my father's building, Ichimanda.

575
00:35:35,933 --> 00:35:37,000
What do you mean?

576
00:35:37,001 --> 00:35:38,568
You don't remember?

577
00:35:38,569 --> 00:35:39,803
Stop making false accusations.

578
00:35:39,804 --> 00:35:41,172
I won't forget.

579
00:35:42,273 --> 00:35:44,108
I'll take whatever you throw at me.

580
00:36:08,533 --> 00:36:12,470
<i>Finally, I can drink it.
My long-awaited Burgundy wine.</i>

581
00:36:17,708 --> 00:36:20,545
<i>Huh? What's going on?</i>

582
00:36:21,979 --> 00:36:23,881
<i>It doesn't taste as good as it used to.</i>

583
00:36:39,564 --> 00:36:40,598
Come in.

584
00:36:41,933 --> 00:36:44,235
President Neo should be returning soon.

585
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:51,409
Time to get changed.

586
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:55,111
- Is there time to eat this?
- Oh,

587
00:36:55,112 --> 00:36:56,647
- probably not.
- Okay.

588
00:37:13,864 --> 00:37:15,398
Good work.

589
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:16,968
- See you again.
- Yes!

590
00:37:18,836 --> 00:37:20,137
Thank you.

591
00:37:20,905 --> 00:37:23,741
Your brother really saved us.

592
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:27,979
It seems studying your diary paid off.

593
00:37:29,013 --> 00:37:31,415
Ai Shinomiya's email said,

594
00:37:32,183 --> 00:37:34,818
"Treasure the one

595
00:37:34,819 --> 00:37:37,021
who loves art and their hometown."

596
00:37:38,322 --> 00:37:39,624
Could that mean Sarasa?

597
00:37:40,758 --> 00:37:43,560
She's a painter
who was featured on NEOXIS TV.

598
00:37:43,561 --> 00:37:46,196
My brother and her are close,

599
00:37:46,197 --> 00:37:49,400
but it feels like more than friends,
less than lovers.

600
00:37:57,975 --> 00:38:01,312
Eito Nomoto is truly no ordinary person.

601
00:38:01,879 --> 00:38:04,314
Yes, there's something about him

602
00:38:04,315 --> 00:38:08,051
that surpasses my understanding.

603
00:38:08,052 --> 00:38:10,220
He predicted the Sochi Olympics results,

604
00:38:10,221 --> 00:38:12,522
Trump's victory,

605
00:38:12,523 --> 00:38:14,190
and saved Neo and the others

606
00:38:14,191 --> 00:38:17,127
from the Paris terrorist attack.

607
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:19,463
He's a truly extraordinary talent.

608
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:23,867
I looked into him.

609
00:38:23,868 --> 00:38:25,969
Apparently, he was hit on the head

610
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:28,606
by a falling object
and hovered between life and death.

611
00:38:29,707 --> 00:38:32,942
That accident may have awakened

612
00:38:32,943 --> 00:38:35,446
a special ability in him.

613
00:38:36,013 --> 00:38:38,749
We have been fortunate
to encounter that talent.

614
00:38:39,517 --> 00:38:42,386
Now it's a matter
of how we make use of it.

615
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:45,956
Come in.

616
00:38:48,359 --> 00:38:49,226
Excuse me.

617
00:38:49,794 --> 00:38:52,095
Thank you for coming. Please, sit down.

618
00:38:52,096 --> 00:38:53,097
Yes.

619
00:38:58,402 --> 00:38:59,904
I asked you here

620
00:39:00,871 --> 00:39:03,407
- to discuss something.
- A discussion?

621
00:39:04,075 --> 00:39:08,478
You recall Neo mentioned wanting
to offer you an employment contract?

622
00:39:08,479 --> 00:39:09,379
Yes.

623
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:12,016
A rival has emerged.

624
00:39:12,883 --> 00:39:14,051
A rival?

625
00:39:14,952 --> 00:39:16,653
Me.

626
00:39:16,654 --> 00:39:19,156
Of course,
I'd offer generous compensation.

627
00:39:22,426 --> 00:39:25,162
So you're asking me to choose

628
00:39:25,830 --> 00:39:27,365
between you and President Neo?

629
00:39:27,932 --> 00:39:30,134
I wouldn't mind if you contract with both.

630
00:39:30,835 --> 00:39:32,536
You're worth that much.

631
00:39:33,971 --> 00:39:34,872
You belong

632
00:39:35,606 --> 00:39:38,943
in a bigger world than this.

633
00:39:39,643 --> 00:39:41,812
You're too talented
for some shopping street!

634
00:39:43,814 --> 00:39:44,815
"Some" shopping street?

635
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:47,551
What's wrong?

636
00:39:49,487 --> 00:39:50,454
Oh, nothing…

637
00:39:57,461 --> 00:39:59,295
- Hey, Eito!
- Don't let him drink too much.

638
00:39:59,296 --> 00:40:00,964
Just a little. Here.

639
00:40:00,965 --> 00:40:02,565
- Thanks.
- Cheers!

640
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:06,404
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

641
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:08,639
- This is great!
- Yeah!

642
00:40:11,475 --> 00:40:13,611
<i>This is so much better
than the wine earlier.</i>

643
00:40:15,813 --> 00:40:16,780
<i>Why is that?</i>

644
00:40:16,781 --> 00:40:18,281
Come on, everyone!

645
00:40:18,282 --> 00:40:20,316
This is Sarasa's home-cooked meal!

646
00:40:20,317 --> 00:40:21,818
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

647
00:40:21,819 --> 00:40:23,787
We have more sake!

648
00:40:23,788 --> 00:40:25,622
Oh! Over here!

649
00:40:25,623 --> 00:40:27,024
Eat up!

650
00:40:28,492 --> 00:40:29,759
- Yeah!
- Eat up!

651
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:33,864
Thank you, Sarasa!

652
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:39,303
Eito, you too!

653
00:40:40,004 --> 00:40:40,905
Here.

654
00:40:42,206 --> 00:40:43,073
<i>What?</i>

655
00:40:44,308 --> 00:40:46,277
<i>Sarasa, who was so cold to me…</i>

656
00:40:47,878 --> 00:40:51,615
I heard you were helping out
at Eri's company, right?

657
00:40:52,483 --> 00:40:54,818
- Well, it's a bit--
- I know.

658
00:40:54,819 --> 00:40:56,253
It's a secret, right?

659
00:41:01,091 --> 00:41:02,493
These are

660
00:41:03,427 --> 00:41:06,897
the stuffed peppers
that you praised the most.

661
00:41:07,665 --> 00:41:08,566
Here.

662
00:41:12,837 --> 00:41:13,704
How is it?

663
00:41:14,638 --> 00:41:15,872
So good!

664
00:41:15,873 --> 00:41:17,073
I'm glad!

665
00:41:17,074 --> 00:41:18,508
Those look good, Sarasa.

666
00:41:18,509 --> 00:41:19,843
Give us some too!

667
00:41:19,844 --> 00:41:23,680
No! These are just for Eito.

668
00:41:23,681 --> 00:41:25,516
- What?
- I'll give you the egg…

669
00:41:26,183 --> 00:41:27,985
<i>What is this feeling of happiness?</i>

670
00:41:29,487 --> 00:41:33,189
<i>This town is becoming
more and more comfortable to be in.</i>

671
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:35,893
Now then…

672
00:41:36,861 --> 00:41:40,063
The poll for the Yagura dance finale song!

673
00:41:40,064 --> 00:41:42,765
- Oh!
- Nice!

674
00:41:42,766 --> 00:41:44,968
So far, <i>Tokyo Ondo</i> leads

675
00:41:44,969 --> 00:41:47,070
<i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i> by one vote.

676
00:41:47,071 --> 00:41:50,473
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

677
00:41:50,474 --> 00:41:53,243
- Huh?
- Has anyone not voted yet?

678
00:41:53,244 --> 00:41:54,611
- What?
- Huh?

679
00:41:54,612 --> 00:41:56,613
Sarasa and Eito haven't yet!

680
00:41:56,614 --> 00:41:58,749
Hey, Sarasa, which will you choose?

681
00:41:59,316 --> 00:42:01,185
Then…

682
00:42:01,852 --> 00:42:02,819
<i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i>.

683
00:42:02,820 --> 00:42:04,487
- Yeah!
- Nice!

684
00:42:04,488 --> 00:42:06,322
It's a tie!

685
00:42:06,323 --> 00:42:07,323
What?

686
00:42:07,324 --> 00:42:09,192
Last one!

687
00:42:09,193 --> 00:42:10,194
Which will it be, Eito?

688
00:42:12,496 --> 00:42:13,663
<i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i>.

689
00:42:13,664 --> 00:42:15,131
Yeah!

690
00:42:15,132 --> 00:42:17,433
Yes! We won!

691
00:42:17,434 --> 00:42:21,037
So, it's 10 to 11.
<i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i> wins!

692
00:42:21,038 --> 00:42:23,707
The finale song is <i>Suki ni Natta Hito</i>!

693
00:42:52,336 --> 00:42:53,771
<i>For some reason,</i>

694
00:42:54,438 --> 00:42:57,408
<i>I kept wishing this moment
would last forever.</i>

695
00:43:07,318 --> 00:43:08,952
Eito!

696
00:43:08,953 --> 00:43:10,787
- Eito!
- Eito!

697
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:12,789
- Eito!
- Call an ambulance!

698
00:43:12,790 --> 00:43:14,424
- Eito!
- Brother, are you okay?

699
00:43:14,425 --> 00:43:16,225
- Eito!
- No! Eito!

700
00:43:16,226 --> 00:43:17,994
- Eito!
- Don't move him!

701
00:43:17,995 --> 00:43:18,928
Keep him like that.

702
00:43:18,929 --> 00:43:20,463
- Call an ambulance!
- Hurry!

703
00:43:20,464 --> 00:43:21,665
MAY 2017

704
00:43:22,633 --> 00:43:24,101
DECEMBER 2018

705
00:43:25,970 --> 00:43:26,804
<i>And…</i>

706
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:29,973
<i>just like in my previous life’s history,</i>

707
00:43:29,974 --> 00:43:33,310
<i>NEOXIS’s new headquarters was ready.</i>

708
00:43:34,211 --> 00:43:38,115
<i>Unlike before, NEOXIS
found greater success in semiconductors,</i>

709
00:43:38,716 --> 00:43:42,585
<i>and Soman thrived in Soman Cards</i>

710
00:43:42,586 --> 00:43:45,189
<i>and the mobile phone business.</i>

711
00:43:46,690 --> 00:43:48,459
<i>In the previous history, this was</i>

712
00:43:49,193 --> 00:43:52,262
<i>when Kosei Neo's isolation
began to deepen,</i>

713
00:43:52,997 --> 00:43:54,798
<i>leading to a series of tragedies.</i>

714
00:43:58,335 --> 00:43:59,536
<i>And…</i>

715
00:44:00,104 --> 00:44:03,474
<i>who is the person who tried to kill me?</i>

716
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:23,593
<i>‎I, as Eito Nomoto, found myself
‎helping the shopping street.</i>

717
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:25,995
<i>‎Will the day come
‎when I will have to pay the price?</i>

718
00:44:25,996 --> 00:44:29,198
‎Won’t you show me this so-called power
‎to see the future as well?

719
00:44:29,199 --> 00:44:31,101
<i>‎May I ask…</i>

720
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:33,102
<i>‎the real reason?</i>

721
00:44:33,103 --> 00:44:34,003
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

722
00:44:34,004 --> 00:44:34,938
Subtitle translation by: Ken Nishizaki
